author: NPR Music
description: Wednesday's, 'Bleeds,' tells the stories of the poets, dreamers, weirdos and freaks – all the people NPR Music's Ann Powers relates to the most. Powers shares how the album represents the South that feels real to her, plus how it showcases how much Karly Hartzman has grown as a vocalist.⁠
title: Wednesday's, 'Bleeds,' tells the stories of the poets, dreamers, weirdos and freaks.
